25|$|Laterites are {{a source}} of {{aluminium}} ore; the ore exists largely in clay minerals and the hydroxides, <b>gibbsite,</b> boehmite, and diaspore, which resembles the composition of bauxite. In Northern Ireland they once provided a major source of iron and aluminium ores. Laterite ores also were the early major source of nickel.|$|E
