50|$|Boehmite {{occurs in}} {{tropical}} laterites and bauxites developed on alumino-silicate bedrock. It also occurs as a hydrothermal alteration product of corundum and nepheline. It occurs with kaolinite, <b>gibbsite</b> and diaspore in bauxite deposits; and with nepheline, <b>gibbsite,</b> diaspore, natrolite and analcime in nepheline pegmatites. Industrially, {{it is used}} as an inexpensive flame retardant additive for fire-safe polymers.|$|E
